<paragraph blockId="1.[136,1452,1848,2091]" lastBlockId="2.[136,1451,158,221]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="101" pageId="1" pageNumber="100">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Foldats" authorityName="Foldats" box="[307,647,1956,1982]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Epidendrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="1" pageNumber="100" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tamaense">
<emphasis box="[307,558,1956,1982]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="100">Epidendrum tamaense</emphasis>
Foldats
</taxonomicName>
(1968: 328; Hágsater in Hágsater &amp; Sánchez 2006: t. 891.), but flowers nearly twice as large, the flowers green to yellow or rarely ivory white, the lip cream suffused with light green at the mid-lobe (
<emphasis box="[253,276,2029,2054]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="100">vs</emphasis>
. olive-green with, lip marked with purple veins); lanceolate to oblong-lanceolate sepals, 3.0–4.0 cm long (
<emphasis box="[145,168,2065,2090]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="100">vs</emphasis>
. elliptic, 2.0 cm long); petals narrowly elliptic, acuminate (
<emphasis box="[851,874,2065,2090]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="100">vs</emphasis>
. narrowly obtrullate, obtuse to acute); the lip with obliquely sub-rectangular to oblong lateral lobes (
<emphasis box="[692,722,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">vs.</emphasis>
sub-orbicular), and the mid-lobe with a short apiculus at the apex and two revolute, obliquely triangular lobes (
<emphasis box="[642,673,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="101">vs.</emphasis>
deeply emarginate, the lobes non revolute, sub-orbicular).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
